dc:subject: Cranium without calotte
Male
Fracture
Atrophy
dc:description: The calotte is missing. While most teeth are present, they consist mostly of broken crowns and roots. There is a healed fracture of the nasal bones and right maxilla. There is calculus on the buccal and occlusal faces of the RM1-2 crowns and mild RM1-2 alveolar resorption. The left styloid process may be atrophied, and there is a deeply excavated tract for the left supraorbital art/vein. There is a notch medially of the occipital condyle (bilateral). Additionally, this skull almost has a left pterygospinous fossa.

dc:memberOf.title: Ford Collection, UM Museum of Anthropological Archaeology
